        <!-- Day 1: Monday 11 Aug -->
        <section class="mb-12">
            <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-teal-700 border-b-2 border-teal-200 pb-2 mb-6">Mon 11 Aug – Welcome to Condesa</h3>
            <div class="space-y-6">
                <article>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">Morning / Early Afternoon: Arrival & Parque México</h4>
                    <p>Arrive, unpack, and let the children stretch their legs on leafy Parque México, with its two playgrounds and charming duck pond.</p>
                    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1625810343484-9709259a43a7?q=80&w=1935&auto=format&fit=crop" alt="Lush green trees and walking path in Parque Mexico" class="mt-4 rounded-lg shadow-md w-full h-64 object-cover">
                </article>
                <article>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">Late Afternoon: Roma–Condesa Food Stroll</h4>
                    <p>Embark on a self-guided food tour featuring churros at El Moro, a fruit-paleta stop at La Michoacana, and a casual fish-taco dinner at El Pescadito.</p>
                    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mt-4">
                        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1579631542720-3a837ea5375a?q=80&w=1964&auto=format&fit=crop" alt="Churros with chocolate dipping sauce" class="rounded-lg shadow-md h-48 w-full object-cover">
                        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1580380826729-ab997f39e4d0?q=80&w=1974&auto=format&fit=crop" alt="Colorful fruit paletas (ice pops)" class="rounded-lg shadow-md h-48 w-full object-cover">
                        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1599974511524-7f037919420a?q=80&w=1974&auto=format&fit=crop" alt="Delicious fish tacos with lime" class="rounded-lg shadow-md h-48 w-full object-cover">
                    </div>
                </article>
                <article>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">Evening Option: Mercado Jamaica</h4>
                    <p>Take a short Uber ride to the flower-filled Mercado Jamaica (open 8 a.m.–6 p.m.) for first-night groceries and a rainbow of photo ops.</p>
                    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1623862412117-15a77db9527f?q=80&w=1974&auto=format&fit=crop" alt="Stalls overflowing with colorful flowers at Mercado Jamaica" class="mt-4 rounded-lg shadow-md w-full h-64 object-cover">
                </article>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Day 2: Tuesday 12 Aug -->
        <section class="mb-12">
            <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-teal-700 border-b-2 border-teal-200 pb-2 mb-6">Tue 12 Aug – Hot-Air Balloon & First Ruins</h3>
            <div class="space-y-6">
                <article>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">04:30 – 13:30: Teotihuacán from Above & Below</h4>
                    <p>An early hotel pick-up for a breathtaking balloon flight over Teotihuacán at sunrise. After a buffet breakfast, walk the ancient Avenue of the Dead and explore the pyramids.</p>
                    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mt-4">
                         <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1568618351563-237b8d933300?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop" alt="Hot air balloons flying over the Teotihuacan pyramids at sunrise" class="rounded-lg shadow-md h-72 w-full object-cover">
                         <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1550043337-ab2b939c4b78?q=80&w=1974&auto=format&fit=crop" alt="The Pyramid of the Sun at Teotihuacan" class="rounded-lg shadow-md h-72 w-full object-cover">
                    </div>
                </article>
                <article>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">Evening (Optional): Lucha Libre</h4>
                    <p>Experience the spectacle of a Lucha Libre family show at Arena México. The kids will love the colorful masks and heroic wrestlers!</p>
                    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1563212897-7477338164bf?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop" alt="Lucha libre wrestlers in the ring" class="mt-4 rounded-lg shadow-md w-full h-64 object-cover">
                </article>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Day 3: Wednesday 13 Aug -->
        <section class="mb-12">
            <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-teal-700 border-b-2 border-teal-200 pb-2 mb-6">Wed 13 Aug – Water & Markets</h3>
            <div class="space-y-6">
                <article>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">06:30 – 09:30: Sunrise Kayak in Xochimilco</h4>
                    <p>A serene start to the day with a sunrise kayak tour in Xochimilco’s protected canals. A quiet, bird-rich, and cooler experience away from the midday crowds.</p>
                    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1626544954130-995a66b9b357?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop" alt="Kayaking in the calm canals of Xochimilco at sunrise" class="mt-4 rounded-lg shadow-md w-full h-64 object-cover">
                </article>
                 <article>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">10:00: Mercado Coyoacán</h4>
                    <p>Enjoy a delicious pozole brunch at Tostadas Coyoacán inside the bustling Mercado Coyoacán.</p>
                    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1681944290325-4c12c3f1a66a?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop" alt="A steaming bowl of traditional Mexican pozole" class="mt-4 rounded-lg shadow-md w-full h-64 object-cover">
                </article>
                <article>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">15:30 – 18:30: Free Time in San Ángel</h4>
                    <p>Relax in San Ángel, known for its tree-lined plazas and excellent coffee shops—a perfect break for the grandparents.</p>
                    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1634533931634-5a8d25593856?q=80&w=1974&auto=format&fit=crop" alt="Cobblestone street and colonial architecture in San Angel" class="mt-4 rounded-lg shadow-md w-full h-64 object-cover">
                </article>
            </div>
        </section>
        
        <!-- Day 4: Thursday 14 Aug -->
        <section class="mb-12">
            <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-teal-700 border-b-2 border-teal-200 pb-2 mb-6">Thu 14 Aug – Chapultepec & Anthropology</h3>
            <div class="space-y-6">
                <article>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">09:00 – 13:00: Museo Nacional de Antropología</h4>
                    <p>Explore one of the world's great museums. Focus on the breathtaking Aztec and Maya halls to see incredible artifacts like the Stone of the Sun.</p>
                    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1616269680252-aa96f554de5e?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop" alt="The Aztec Sun Stone at the National Museum of Anthropology" class="mt-4 rounded-lg shadow-md w-full h-64 object-cover">
                </article>
                <article>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">Lunch & Afternoon: Chapultepec Park</h4>
                    <p>Enjoy a picnic lunch on Chapultepec Lake, followed by a row-boat rental and a walk through the vast Bosque de Chapultepec.</p>
                    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1605823861299-8551b98a4d7d?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop" alt="Row boats on the lake in Chapultepec Park with the castle in the background" class="mt-4 rounded-lg shadow-md w-full h-64 object-cover">
                </article>
                 <article>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">Evening: Pastry Stop</h4>
                    <p>Pop into the famous La Panadería Rosetta for some of the city's best pastries on your way home.</p>
                    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1621939514649-280e25b93864?q=80&w=1974&auto=format&fit=crop" alt="A selection of delicious pastries from a bakery" class="mt-4 rounded-lg shadow-md w-full h-64 object-cover">
                </article>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Day 5: Friday 15 Aug -->
        <section class="mb-12">
            <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-teal-700 border-b-2 border-teal-200 pb-2 mb-6">Fri 15 Aug – Historic Center & Mexicable</h3>
            <div class="space-y-6">
                <article>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">09:30 – 13:00: Historic Center</h4>
                    <p>A guided walk of the Zócalo, the Templo Mayor excavations, and the stunning murals inside the Palacio Nacional.</p>
                    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1599831022033-333335504245?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop" alt="The Zocalo, Mexico City's main square, with the Metropolitan Cathedral" class="mt-4 rounded-lg shadow-md w-full h-64 object-cover">
                </article>
                <article>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">14:30 – 17:30: Mexicable Ride</h4>
                    <p>Head north to ride Mexicable Line 2. Soar above colorful hillside murals and hop off at La Cañada viewpoint for a playground break.</p>
                    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1678239011579-6345b5500d3d?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop" alt="View from the Mexicable cable car over colorful houses on a hillside" class="mt-4 rounded-lg shadow-md w-full h-64 object-cover">
                </article>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Day 6: Saturday 16 Aug -->
        <section class="mb-12">
            <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-teal-700 border-b-2 border-teal-200 pb-2 mb-6">Sat 16 Aug – Frida, Anahuacalli & Bazaar Sábado</h3>
            <div class="space-y-6">
                <article>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">10:00 – 11:30: Frida Kahlo House (Casa Azul)</h4>
                    <p>Visit the iconic blue house where Frida Kahlo was born, lived, and died. Book your timed entry tickets well in advance!</p>
                    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1599134842148-a79137e7642b?q=80&w=1974&auto=format&fit=crop" alt="The bright blue exterior of the Frida Kahlo Museum (Casa Azul)" class="mt-4 rounded-lg shadow-md w-full h-64 object-cover">
                </article>
                <article>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">11:45: Museo Diego Rivera-Anahuacalli</h4>
                    <p>A short taxi ride takes you to this unique pyramid-like museum designed by Diego Rivera to house his collection of pre-Hispanic art.</p>
                    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1669861933923-a46a5639423d?q=80&w=1932&auto=format&fit=crop" alt="The imposing volcanic stone structure of the Museo Anahuacalli" class="mt-4 rounded-lg shadow-md w-full h-64 object-cover">
                </article>
                 <article>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">16:00 – 18:00: Bazaar Sábado</h4>
                    <p>Browse the famous Bazaar Sábado arts-and-crafts market in San Ángel, a Saturday-only institution.</p>
                    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1573071353664-63300a73369a?q=80&w=1974&auto=format&fit=crop" alt="Colorful crafts and textiles at an outdoor market" class="mt-4 rounded-lg shadow-md w-full h-64 object-cover">
                </article>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Day 7: Sunday 17 Aug -->
        <section class="mb-12">
            <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-teal-700 border-b-2 border-teal-200 pb-2 mb-6">Sun 17 Aug – Hands-on Cooking & Park Play</h3>
            <div class="space-y-6">
                <article>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">10:30 – 14:00: Private Mexican Cooking Class</h4>
                    <p>A hands-on cooking class in your Airbnb. The whole family can get involved, from mashing avocados for guacamole to learning the secrets of mole.</p>
                    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1547592180-85f173990554?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop" alt="Hands preparing fresh ingredients for a Mexican meal" class="mt-4 rounded-lg shadow-md w-full h-64 object-cover">
                </article>
                <article>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">15:30 – 18:00: Parque La Mexicana</h4>
                    <p>Head to the modern Parque La Mexicana in Santa Fe for huge playgrounds, scooter paths, and great sunset skyline views before grabbing dinner from the food trucks.</p>
                    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1678239011286-1a52866d997a?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop" alt="Modern playground and skate park at Parque La Mexicana with city skyline" class="mt-4 rounded-lg shadow-md w-full h-64 object-cover">
                </article>
            </div>
        </section>
        
        <!-- Day 8: Monday 18 Aug -->
        <section class="mb-12">
            <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-teal-700 border-b-2 border-teal-200 pb-2 mb-6">Mon 18 Aug – Souvenirs & Departure</h3>
            <div class="space-y-6">
                <article>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">Morning: Last-Minute Souvenirs</h4>
                    <p>A quick run to Mercado de Artesanías La Ciudadela for any last-minute souvenirs or back to Roma for some locally grown coffee beans to take home.</p>
                    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1563911592138-58a088733f95?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop" alt="Colorful skulls and crafts at Mercado de Artesanias La Ciudadela" class="mt-4 rounded-lg shadow-md w-full h-64 object-cover">
                </article>
                 <article>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">Departure</h4>
                    <p>Transfer to the airport, allowing at least 1.5 hours for the journey on a weekday morning. ¡Buen viaje!</p>
                </article>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Extra Tips Section -->
        <section class="bg-teal-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-teal-800 mb-4">Extra Tips for a Smoother Week</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-teal-900">
                <li><strong>Altitude & Sun:</strong> CDMX sits at 7,300 ft; keep everyone hydrated and apply SPF 50 every morning.</li>
                <li><strong>Transport:</strong> Install the Didi and Beat ride-hailing apps. For the 2-year-old, pack a fold-up Mifold or similar travel car seat.</li>
                <li><strong>Cash:</strong> Markets and trajineras (Xochimilco boats) are often cash-only. ATMs are plentiful but withdraw mid-week to avoid weekend lines.</li>
                <li><strong>Stroller Logistics:</strong> Most Metro/BRT stations now have elevators, but sidewalks can be uneven; a rugged stroller is a good idea.</li>
                <li><strong>Safety After Dark:</strong> Stick to the well-lit, pedestrian-friendly cores of Condesa/Roma, Coyoacán, San Ángel, and the Zócalo in the evenings.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

